HEADWORD: Muriated
<hw>Mu"ri*a`ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Put in
brine.</def> <rj><au>Evelyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Combined or impregnated with
muriatic or hydrochloric acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Photog.)</fld> <def>Prepared with chloride of
silver through the agency of common salt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muriatic</ent>⟦br⟧
